      "content": "i was just looking at some photos from the james webb telescope and it just hit me... like, everything we do, every single thing, is just a blip. in a few billion years the sun dies, then the universe just goes cold and dark. literally nothing survives. why am i even bothering to get out of bed or try to do anything when it's all just going to be erased anyway? it feels like a cruel joke.",
